cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.DC

The paper proposes a deep neural network-based solution for arithmetic encoding, which involves modeling large context while maintaining computational efficiency. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Multimedia (cs.MM), Information Theory (cs.IT), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). However, given that the paper focuses on image compression and specifically mentions lossless gray image compression, cs.MM and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions real-time encoding speed, which could suggest a focus on efficient implementation, further supporting the possibility of cs.MM as a likely sub-category.
